(j) i s in breach of confidence by-
(i) d ivulging any matter which it is his duty to keep secret;
(ii) giving notice, directly or indirectly, to any person against whom any
warrant or summons has been or is about to be issued, except in
the lawful execution of such warrant or summons;
(iii) c ommunicating to the public, press or to any unauthorised person,
any confidential matter concerning the National Parks and Wildlife
Service;
(iv) s howing to any person outside the National Parks and Wildlife
Service any book or written or printed document the property of the
National Parks and Wildlife Service without proper authority;
(v) making or joining in making, any anonymous communication to a
wildlife police officer superior in rank to him;
